      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not sure if this is a good idea, but I guess we can see how it goes and adjust if necessary.\n\nSpecifically:\n\n1. No one is watching the tree during these times, so if a roll breaks things, it will take several hours before the Sheriff sees the breakage.\n\n2. If the roll fails (and it\u0027s not a flaky failure), one of two things will happen:\n  a. If there are new commits to the child, the roll will be closed and won\u0027t be retried until the next day. AFAICT, there\u0027s no way for the Sheriff to retry after a fix is committed, so if the fix doesn\u0027t work, the following night\u0027s roll will contain 2+ days of commits in one roll. Also, not clear if the sheriff will notice when the roll only fails once, so it may take 2+ days to get a fix.\n  b. Otherwise, the roller will keep +2ing and retrying the failure, even though no one is around to notice that things are failing.",
